      <h2>REST  behavior</h2>
      <p>The primary focus of the DARTS Service Provider is to support the de-identify and anonymize operation.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Security:</b>
      </p>
      <p>Implementations must meet the general security requirements documented in FHIR <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/security.html">Security guidance</a>.</p>
      <p><span class="conformance">In addition the DARTS Service Provider **SHOULD** meet the security requirements as outlined in the <a href="spec.html#smart-on-fhir-backend-services-authorization">SMART on FHIR Backend Services Authorization</a></span></p>
       
        <h3>FHIR Operations summary</h3>
        <p><span class="conformance">The following FHIR operations SHALL be supported by the DARTS Service Provider</span></p>
      
